fields.name: Espresso
fields.brief_description: A single shot of the house blend  to perk you up - as stong as they come!
fields.description:
An espresso, or a short black, as it’s commonly called is essentially 30ml of strong brewed coffee.  It's brewed by forcing a small amount of nearly boiling water, under pressure (steam), through finely ground coffee beans.

Espresso can be made from a wide variety of coffee beans - at espressOrders we use a house blend sourced from our Fairtrade coffee partners.

fields.name: Latte
fields.brief_description: Espresso, topped with steamed milk and a layer of foamed milk crema
fields.description: A caffe latte, often shortened to latte, is made with an espresso shot,  steamed milk and with a layer of foamed milk crema.

fields.name: Cappuccino
fields.brief_description: Espresso with steamed milk and froth on top
fields.description:
Recognised by the froth on top, a cappuccino is comprised of one-third espresso shot, one-third textured milk and one-third froth on top.
 
Just ask if you'd like a dusting of chocolate or cinnamon to finish!
